# Histology analysis - EpiClim F0 Liver
Histopathological analysis of adult female zebrafish liver following developmental exposure to combined climate stressors and PFOS.

## Files
- `.Rmd` — Analysis source code
- `.html` — Rendered analysis
- `.xlsx` file — Input data (cell density and vacuole area measurements + metadata)

## Analysis pipeline
- Image analysis: QuPath v0.5.1 (x64)
- Endpoints: cell density (cell detection tool) and vacuole area (pixel threshold tool)
- Quantification: 3 quadrats (250 × 250 µm) per section
- Statistical analysis: robust linear models on section-level means (to avoid pseudo-replication)
- Model design: ~ condition + exposure batch
- Multiple comparisons: emmeans with Dunnett's method (vs Control) and Benjamini-Hochberg (pairwise)
- Sensitivity analysis: confirmed robustness of results after excluding preliminary exposure batch

## Data
- **Samples**: 37 adult females (n = 3-5 per condition)

## Reproducibility
To reproduce the analyses:
1. Clone this repository
2. Open the .Rmd file in RStudio
3. Ensure the input data files are in the same folder as the .Rmd
4. Install required packages listed in the setup chunk
5. Run all chunks in order or knit the document

Package versions used in this analysis are documented in the sessionInfo output at the end of the rendered HTML.
